## Link to this sectionPython Integration#

For easier integration, use the Ultralytics Python package which handles authentication, uploads, and real-time metric streaming automatically.

### Link to this sectionInstallation & Setup#
    
    
    pip install ultralytics

Verify installation:
    
    
    yolo check

Package Version Requirement

Platform integration requires **ultralytics >=8.4.60**. Lower versions will NOT work with Platform.

### Link to this sectionAuthentication#
    
    
    yolo settings api_key=YOUR_API_KEY

### Link to this sectionUsing Platform Datasets#

Reference datasets with `ul://` URIs:
    
    
    from ultralytics import YOLO
    
    model = YOLO("yolo26n.pt")
    
    # Train on your Platform dataset
    model.train(
        data="ul://your-username/datasets/your-dataset",
        epochs=100,
        imgsz=640,
    )

**URI Format:**

Pattern| Description  
---|---  
`ul://username/datasets/slug`| Dataset  
`ul://username/project-name`| Project  
`ul://username/project/model-name`| Specific model  
`ul://ultralytics/yolo26/yolo26n`| Official model  
  
### Link to this sectionPushing to Platform#

Send results to a Platform project:
    
    
    from ultralytics import YOLO
    
    model = YOLO("yolo26n.pt")
    
    # Results automatically sync to Platform
    model.train(
        data="coco8.yaml",
        epochs=100,
        project="your-username/my-project",
        name="experiment-1",
    )

**What syncs:**

  * Training metrics (real-time)
  * Final model weights
  * Validation plots
  * Console output
  * System metrics



### Link to this sectionAPI Examples#

**Load a model from Platform:**
    
    
    # Your own model
    model = YOLO("ul://username/project/model-name")
    
    # Official model
    model = YOLO("ul://ultralytics/yolo26/yolo26n")

**Run inference:**
    
    
    results = model("image.jpg")
    
    # Access results
    for r in results:
        boxes = r.boxes  # Detection boxes
        masks = r.masks  # Segmentation masks
        keypoints = r.keypoints  # Pose keypoints
        probs = r.probs  # Classification probabilities

**Export model:**
    
    
    # Export to ONNX
    model.export(format="onnx", imgsz=640, half=True)
    
    # Export to TensorRT
    model.export(format="engine", imgsz=640, half=True)
    
    # Export to CoreML
    model.export(format="coreml", imgsz=640)

**Validation:**
    
    
    metrics = model.val(data="ul://username/datasets/my-dataset")
    
    print(f"mAP50: {metrics.box.map50}")
    print(f"mAP50-95: {metrics.box.map}")

